    supports HTML5 video This is a modal window. Beginning of dialog window. Escape will cancel and close the window. End of dialog window.  Ndlozi said the coronavirus was called the invisible enemy however the men who committed femicide were not invisible. “You can fight this struggle. Women of South Africa, you have to come together and you can confront this… You don’t need anyone’s authority to confront this system,” he said. The MP called for all South African men to isolate rapists, woman beaters and men who undermine women amongst them.